721710f-a.title: Manhattan: Morningside Avenue - 114th Street (West)
721710f-a.text:
Morningside (left) and Manhattan (right) Avenue's, north
from West 114th Street, and showing the small triangular
park at this point. Standing in the latter is the Lafa-
yette Monument. Morningside Park is at the extreme left
tho it does not appear.
No. 1: November, 1904
1906

721709f-a.title: Manhattan: Morningside Avenue - 114th Street (West)
721709f-a.text:
Morningside (left) and Manhattan (right) Avenues,
at W. 114 th Street, showing the Washington and Lafa-
yette Statue. Placque on same reads ''Lafayette-Wash-
ington, presented to the City of New York by Chas. S.
Rouss, April 19, 1900''. Incidentally the donor, a
merchant, was popularly known as ''Broadway Rouss''.
Belonging to the late 90's he started as a peddler and
thru thrift and enterprise he developed a huge organi-
zation with headquarters on Broadway.
1920
